Start  
  ↓  
Login to Azure Portal  
(Open https://portal.azure.com and sign in)  
  ↓  
Go to "Virtual Machines"  
(Search from dashboard or use sidebar menu)  
  ↓  
Click "Create" → Select "Azure Virtual Machine"  
  ↓  
Configure Basics  
- Select Subscription  
- Create / Choose Resource Group  
- Enter VM Name  
- Select Region (Location)  
  ↓  
Select OS Image  
- Ubuntu (Linux) OR  
- Windows Server  
  ↓  
Choose VM Size  
- Select CPU & RAM configuration  
- Example: B1s (Free Tier)  
  ↓  
Set Authentication  
- Choose Username  
- Select Authentication Type:  
   → SSH Key (Recommended for Linux)  
   → Password  
  ↓  
Configure Networking  
- Create Virtual Network (VNet)  
- Assign Public IP  
- Open Required Ports:  
   → 22 (SSH - Linux)  
   → 3389 (RDP - Windows)  
   → 80 (HTTP)  
   → 443 (HTTPS)  
  ↓  
Review + Create  
(Check all configurations carefully)  
  ↓  
Validation Process  
(Azure checks for errors)  
  ↓  
Deployment in Progress  
(Resources are being created)  
  ↓  
VM Successfully Created  
(Status: Running)  
  ↓  
Connect to VM  
- SSH (Linux): using terminal  
- RDP (Windows): using Remote Desktop  
  ↓  
Post Setup  
- Install software  
- Configure server / applications  
  ↓  
End  
